div.p:
Some say that inferiour Levites did intermeddle in secular affaires. But I answere, there were Levites of two sorts; out of one sort, Priests were chosen, (out of Aarons Line;) the others were like the Seculars among the Iesuites. And these last did (as the Seculars do
                        •
                     ) performe the Civill part of those Religious Services; and nothing else, that I can finde in Scripture, or Story.

You see here what Power we give to Synods and Councels, or all other Churches over one particular Church; 
                        •
                     o wit, a counselling, perswading (which sure is very prevailing) but not commanding Authority.
